Since Barcelona he’s taken over two overloaded teams that have had no problem winning their domestic league titles, he went to each club with one Objective and ONE OBJECTIVE ONLY - The Champions League.

He’s been unable to win it - with great teams and essentially unlimited financial resources. Yet he still complains about not having enough to spend.

Klopp is a class manager.

snippet.authorDisplayName: Henk Williem Adriannus van der Napier
snippet.textDisplay:
As a Liverpool fan, the only statistic I care is the number of trophies/awards won. Statistics like the longest unbeaten streak, the best start, season’s invicibility, youngest/oldest player fielded, most points collected and all statistics of the same type means nothing to me.

I bet not many people knows that Nottingham Forest hold a 42-match unbeaten streak until Liverpool equalized it this week.

snippet.textDisplay:
When the media loves you they love you. They keep making excuses for city and Pep. How dare they talk about injuries for a team that they’ve told us all along their ‘B team’ would make top 4. All the while they pour hate daily on Ole and Utd who’ve had to deal with worse injuries and are in the first year of a rebuilding project....

As for today’s game, some of the worst refereeing I’ve witnessed in a while - and that’s saying something! The EPL has bungled VAR so bad, I just don’t have faith anymore that VAR is worth the headaches. Seems to me so many calls are still coming down to subjective calls and if that’s the case, just let the ref on the field make the call...

1. Sterling should’ve seen straight red for the Dele challenge. We’ve seen at least 3 or 4 similar challenges this term result in reds already. Something tells me if it was A Burnley player on, say Kun, that’d been red.
2. If Loris didn’t bring sterling down for the pk, then it has to be a second yellow for diving. It can’t just be nothing. VAR was brought in to give finality to cases such as these. I noticed, they didn’t give fans the close-up slow motion shot to see if Hugo makes contact or not.
3. That whole Hugo/Raheem incident shouldn’t have mattered anyways to begin with. VAR replays clearly show Hugo a foot off his line when the Ilkay makes contact with the ball from the spot. That’s a clear PK re-take. Weird thing is the commentators made no mention of it and neither did the in-studio pundits at half time and even the post match analysis on most of these shows
